  "text": "The original indicators of social quality, developed by the ENISQ, were developed into a questionnaire, which was tested for both validity and reliability [CITATION_1] , including collaboration and agreement with the originators of the social quality indicators [CITATION_2] . The questionnaire had 50 questions, divided into the four conditional factors: 4 questions related to socio-economic security, 11 questions related to social inclusion, 5 questions related to social cohesion, 19 questions related to social empowerment, and 11 demographic questions (the full questionnaire is available on-line -see Additional File 1).",
